## Complexity Analysis

| Operation | Per Step | Total (T steps) |
|-----------|----------|-----------------|
| Forward pass | O(1) input, O(N+t) attention over cached keys | O(T·(N+T)) attention |
| Entropy computation | O(V) where V = vocab size | O(T·V) |
| Top-k extraction | O(V·log(k)) via torch.topk | O(T·V·log(k)) |
| Hidden state extraction | O(D) per layer × 3 layers | O(T·D·3) |
| Token decode | O(1) | O(T) |

**Total: O(T·(N+T) + T·V)** — dominated by the attention computation, identical to `model.generate()`.

---

## Memory Analysis

| Component | Size | Notes |
|-----------|------|-------|
| KV cache | O(T·L·D) | L=layers, D=hidden_dim. Grows linearly. Same as generate(). |
| Logits tensor | O(V) | Only one step's logits live on GPU at a time |
| Top-k stored | O(T·k) | k=5, extremely small |
| Entropy stored | O(T) | One float per step |
| Hidden states stored | O(T·D·3) | 3 layers, moved to CPU immediately |

**Key memory optimizations:**
- Hidden states are `.detach().cpu()` immediately — they don't accumulate on GPU
- Only top-5 logits are retained per step, not the full vocab distribution
- KV cache is deleted after decoding completes
- `torch.cuda.empty_cache()` called at teardown

**For Qwen2.5-1.5B on RTX 4060 (8GB):**
- Model weights: ~3 GB (fp16)
- KV cache (512 tokens): ~0.5 GB
- Working memory: ~0.5 GB
- Total: ~4 GB — comfortably within 8 GB

